The paper deals with deploying deep models on embedded devices for vision tasks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new fixed-point network for quantization of data, which involves optimization techniques and neural network architecture design, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed network on face detection tasks, which falls under augmented reality (cs.AR) sub-category.
